com.navis.framework.persistence.event

Interface ITxnCommitEntityEventFilter<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - class of the event to be filtered
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ITxnCommitEntityAuditEventFilter
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractTxnCommitEntityEventFilter, EventBusCommitEventFilter

    public interface ITxnCommitEntityEventFilter<E>
    This interface represents a transaction PRE COMMIT filter associated with a ITxnCommitEntityEventInterceptor, where the entity event data saved is filtered and the desired data fields are saved for POST COMMIT processing.
    Author:
    Gisella Saavedra, Mar 16, 2012
    See Also:
    ITxnCommitEntityEventInterceptor

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      ValueHolder filter(int inEventType, E inEvent)
      Filters the entity audit event as specified by the parameters for the filter registration.
      void registerEntityAuditEvent(EntityId inEntityId, int inAuditEventType, MetafieldIdList inFldListThatChanged, MetafieldIdList inFldListToKeep)
      Registers the entity represented by inEntityId for the event inAuditEventType where if there is any changed in the entity fields specified in the list inFldListThatChanged, event data will be saved and the entity field values specified by inFldListToKeep will be saved for later processing, at the POST COMMIT phase.

        Registers the entity represented by inEntityId for the event inAuditEventType where if there is any changed in the entity fields specified in the list inFldListThatChanged, event data will be saved and the entity field values specified by inFldListToKeep will be saved for later processing, at the POST COMMIT phase.
        Parameters:
        inEntityId - entity ID
        inAuditEventType - entity event type
        inFldListThatChanged - list of fields to observe changes in
        inFldListToKeep - list of fields to keep if the entity passed the filter
